      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: add inbound peer send policy matching",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds native `session.sendPolicy.rules[].match.peerEquals: \"inboundPeer\"` support.\n- Allows relational send-policy checks between the outbound target and the inbound peer for the current automatic-delivery turn, including `identityLinks` aliases.\n- Threads inbound peer context through automatic replies, routed replies, tool context, plugin/gateway message-action context, and durable outbound delivery.\n- Keeps send-policy-only predicates out of shared allow/deny scopes.\n- Preserves explicit `message.send` compatibility by keeping explicit gateway/plugin/direct sends outside `session.sendPolicy` suppression.\n- Reports blocked automatic durable sends as `denied_by_send_policy` suppression outcomes.\n- Adds focused unit coverage and docs/help labels for the new predicate.\n\nFixes #85175.\n\n## Verification\n\nLatest head explicit-gateway-send follow-up validated locally: `fa5474b29b`.\n\nClean local worktree used: `~/projects/openclaw-pr-85763-send-policy`.\n\nCommands run against latest head:\n\n```text\npnpm install --frozen-lockfile\npnpm exec vitest run src/sessions/send-policy.test.ts --config test/vitest/vitest.unit-fast.config.ts\npnpm exec vitest run src/infra/outbound/message-action-runner.plugin-dispatch.test.ts --config test/vitest/vitest.infra.config.ts\nnode scripts/test-projects.mjs test/scripts/real-behavior-proof-policy.test.ts\n```\n\nEarlier broad validation on head `5b0f312431` before the schema-only follow-up:\n\n```text\npnpm protocol:check\npnpm lint\npnpm check:test-types\nOPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/gateway/server-startup-post-attach.test.ts\n```\n\nObserved local results on latest head:\n\n```text\npnpm install --frozen-lockfile already up to date\nsrc/sessions/send-policy.test.ts passed 13/13 tests\nsrc/infra/outbound/message-action-runner.plugin-dispatch.test.ts passed 21/21 tests\ntest/scripts/real-behavior-proof-policy.test.ts passed 23/23 tests\n```\n\nEarlier broad validation results on head `5b0f312431`:\n\n```text\npnpm protocol:check passed\npnpm lint passed with 0 warnings and 0 errors\npnpm check:test-types passed\nsrc/gateway/server-startup-post-attach.test.ts passed 39/39 tests\n```\n\nEarlier focused send-policy validation on this branch:\n\n```text\npnpm test src/sessions/send-policy.test.ts src/config/schema.hints.test.ts src/cli/config-cli.test.ts src/infra/outbound/message.test.ts src/infra/outbound/outbound-send-service.test.ts src/agents/tools/message-tool.test.ts src/infra/outbound/message-action-runner.plugin-dispatch.test.ts\npnpm check:changed\n```\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: `sendPolicy` can now allow same-peer automatic delivery and suppress wrong-peer automatic outbound delivery when `peerEquals: \"inboundPeer\"` is configured.\n\nReal environment tested: local OpenClaw source checkout on Linux, clean worktree `~/projects/openclaw-pr-85763-send-policy`, branch `fix/send-policy-peer-equals-inbound-peer`, latest head `fa5474b29b`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: from the clean PR worktree, ran `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`, ran the focused send-policy unit test, ran the gateway explicit-send regression test, and ran the real-behavior-proof policy test. Earlier on this branch, regenerated and checked protocol artifacts, ran lint, ran test type checks, ran the gateway startup regression test, ran focused send-policy shards, and ran `check:changed` before the final schema follow-up.\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\nLatest head terminal capture:\n\n```text\npnpm install --frozen-lockfile already up to date\nsrc/sessions/send-policy.test.ts passed 13/13 tests\ntest/scripts/real-behavior-proof-policy.test.ts passed 23/23 tests\n```\n\nEarlier broad validation terminal capture:\n\n```text\npnpm protocol:check passed\npnpm lint passed with 0 warnings and 0 errors\npnpm check:test-types passed\nsrc/gateway/server-startup-post-attach.test.ts passed 39/39 tests\n```\n\nEarlier terminal capture from the focused send-policy run:\n\n```text\n[test] passed 5 Vitest shards in 32.58s\n```\n\nEarlier terminal capture from `pnpm check:changed`:\n\n```text\n[check:changed] typecheck core\n[check:changed] typecheck core tests\n[check:changed] lint core\nruntime-sidecar-loaders: local runtime sidecar loaders look OK.\nImport cycle check: 0 runtime value cycle(s).\n```\n\nThe tests cover same-peer allow, wrong-peer denial metadata, missing inbound peer behavior, `identityLinks` alias comparison, schema split rejection for shared scopes, inbound peer propagation, and automatic message-action send-policy suppression before transport.\n\nObserved result after fix: same-peer configured automatic sends are allowed when the outbound target equals a trusted inbound peer candidate; wrong-peer automatic sends are denied/suppressed before transport with `send_policy_peer_mismatch` / `denied_by_send_policy` metadata. Explicit `message.send` compatibility is preserved by keeping explicit gateway/plugin/direct sends outside `session.sendPolicy` suppression.\n\nWhat was not tested: no private Telegram credentials, IPs, phone numbers, API keys, or non-public endpoints are included here. Live Telegram proof has not been posted in this PR yet; if a maintainer or Mantis captures redacted Telegram proof, it can be appended as stronger external evidence.\n\n",
